The crucial part is how it deals with reduction trees. Currently, it considers single-node trees as non-vectorizable for reductions. The problem is that a single node CAN be part of a reduction. If the node is a gather, which gathers values from other reductions. So, the existing check is overly aggressive in certain cases.

